data.title: A must visit
data.text: This little gem has been here for many years and nothing has changed. The food is delicious with a good variety. On the weekends they offer a whole cabeza de borrego, which translates to (don't get grossed out till you try it), sheep's head. It is steamed to perfection. The menudo is one of the best around, perfect for the hangover. If you are looking for that quintessential authentic hole in the wall restaurant, this is your spot.
